$ R function: sprintf

`sprintf` is a wrapper around the → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/C/libc/functions/printf[C function `printf`].

{ Basic usage

  gh|about-r|/functions/sprintf/basic.R||

}
{ Omitting quotes

  The output of `sprintf` embeds strings in quotes. These can be omitted by feeding the output of `sprintf` to → development/languages/R/functions/cat[`cat(…)`]:

  gh|about-r|/functions/sprintf/omit-quotes.R||

}
{ Using the recycling rule

  The *recycling rule* can be applied in `sprintf`:
  gh|about-r|/functions/sprintf/recycling-rule.R||

}


